# {{theology}} {{Christianity}} A formerly prevalent [[heresy]] now condemned by quite nearly all Christian denominations, which regards [[Judaism]] as not merely having been supplanted by Christianity, but that the [[covenant]] between God and Israel as His chosen people has been abrogated. The concept of [[deicide]] is a motif of the heresy.
 
